The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Beck banned for two years

London: Karol Beck of Slovakia has been banned for two years for doping, the International Tennis Federation (ITF) said on Monday. 

 Beck tested positive for the anabolic agent clenbuterol last September during Slovakias Davis Cup World Group semi-final against Argentina. 

His results in the tie are automatically disqualified. 

